'''Patrick Wimmer''' (born 30 May 2001) is an Austrian professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Midfielder#Winger|right winger]] for [[Bundesliga]] club [[VfL Wolfsburg]] and the [[Austria national football team|Austria national team]].<ref>{{Worldfootball.net|patrick-wimmer|new_id=pe602069}}</ref>

==Club career==
On 13 April 2022, Wimmer signed a five-year contract with [[VfL Wolfsburg]], beginning with the 2022–23 season.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=VfL Wolfsburg|url=https://www.vfl-wolfsburg.de/newsdetails/news-detail/detail/news/wimmer-wird-ein-wolf|title=Wimmer wird ein Wolf|date=13 April 2022|access-date=22 July 2022|language=de}}</ref>

==International career==
Wimmer was called up to the [[Austria national football team|senior Austria squad]] for the [[2022–23 UEFA Nations League A|UEFA Nations League]] matches against  [[Croatia national football team|Croatia]], [[Denmark national football team|Denmark]], [[France national football team|France]] and [[Denmark national football team|Denmark]] on 3, 6, 10 and 13 June 2022.<ref>{{cite news 
|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/61766082
|title=Austria 1–1 France
|publisher=BBC Sport 
|date=10 June 2022 |access-date=13 June 2022}}</ref>

